      &lt;img alt="" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-SoCBAgByOPdtVOnetBJToHCZVA=/0x0:2898x1932/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73611000/Image_1.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Credit: Blue Origin&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="oQVTbW"&gt;Blue Origin’s New Glenn rocket &lt;a href="https://www.blueorigin.com/news/new-glenn-completes-second-stage-hotfire"&gt;hit a significant milestone this week&lt;/a&gt;, completing its first second-stage hot fire test that validates the interactions between the subsystems, its two BE-3U engines, and the ground control systems. The test lasted for 15 seconds and allowed the launch operations team to practice launch procedures in the lead-up to New Glenn’s planned November launch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="0XwQ9w"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Jeff Bezos unveils the design of Blue Origin’s future orbital rocket — the New Glenn","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2016/9/12/12887580/blue-origin-orbital-rocket-design-announced-new-glenn"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="HWgT8i"&gt;New Glenn is Blue Origin’s big rocket answer to SpaceX when it comes &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24001656/jeff-bezos-elon-musk-space-blue-origin-rivalry"&gt;to shooting things into space&lt;/a&gt;, but Jeff Bezos’ company has been &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2021/2/25/22301172/jeff-bezos-blue-origin-delays-new-glenn-2022"&gt;moving slowly&lt;/a&gt; and has only so far conducted tourist flights to suborbital space using its New Shepard rocket. New Glenn was supposed to launch the smallsat ESCAPADE in conjunction with NASA this year as its first mission, but it...&lt;/p&gt;
