  &lt;p id="uKsp4u"&gt;Taito Corporation, which &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2013/10/20/4856148/space-invaders-creator-says-hes-terrible-at-the-game"&gt;gave the world &lt;em&gt;Space Invaders&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; over 45 years ago, has collaborated with the designers of Floor 84 Studio to create a watch that pairs retro gaming with basic health tracking capabilities. The &lt;a href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20240924896062/en/Blasting-Through-Time-SPACE-INVADERS%E2%84%A2-Joins-Forces-with-My-Play-Watch-and-Floor-84-Studio"&gt;Space Invaders: My Play Watch&lt;/a&gt; is now available for $60 for the earliest backers of a &lt;a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/f84/space-invaderstm-my-play-watch?ref=hodqsx"&gt;Kickstarter crowdfunding campaign&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="Qdxc9O"&gt;The My Play Watch was &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/10/24240947/this-apple-watch-clones-best-feature-is-a-playable-version-of-space-invaders"&gt;teased earlier this month&lt;/a&gt;, but we now know more about what its creators say it can do. Its design looks inspired by, or directly lifted from, the Apple Watch, but with a 1.86-inch touchscreen display and a body that’s not as thin as the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/9/24236801/apple-watch-series-10-price-specs-features-release-date"&gt;Series 10&lt;/a&gt; or as thick as the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/19/24248380/apple-watch-ultra-2-black-smartwatch-wearables"&gt;Ultra 2&lt;/a&gt;. It comes with two watch straps that match its retro gaming aesthetic, and it’s compatible with standard 22mm...&lt;/p&gt;
